{"title_page": "Jimin (singer, born 1995)", "text_new": "{{pp-blp|small=yes}}\n{{short description|South Korean singer, songwriter, and dancer}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Korean name|Park}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Jimin\n| image              = Park Ji-min for Dispatch White Day Special, 27 February 2019 03.jpg\n| alt                = Jimin rests his head on his hand and smiles\n| caption            = Jimin for ''Dispatch'' magazine, February 2019\n| native_name        = \uc9c0\ubbfc\n| birth_name         = Park Ji-min\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1995|10|13}}\n| birth_place        = [[Geumjeong District]], [[Busan]], South Korea\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Singer|songwriter|dancer}}\n| awards             = [[File:ROK_Order_of_Cultural_Merit_Hwa-gwan_(5th_Class)_ribbon.PNG|border|23px]] [[Order of Cultural Merit (Korea)|Hwagwan Order of Cultural Merit]] (2018)\n| net_worth          = \n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background         = solo_singer\n| genre              = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[Alternative R&B]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Herman |first1=Tamar |title=BTS Reveal 'Serendipity' Comeback Trailer for 'Love Yourself: Her' Album |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/7950090/bts-jimin-serendipity-love-yourself-her-album-k-pop-south-korea |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=September 7, 2018|date=September 4, 2018}}</ref>}}\n| instrument         = Vocals\n| label              = [[Big Hit Entertainment|Big Hit]]\n| years_active       = 2013\u2013present \n| associated_acts    = [[BTS]] \n}} <!-- end module1 -->\n| module2            = {{Infobox Korean name | child = yes\n| hangul = {{linktext|\ubc15|\uc9c0|\ubbfc}} \n| hanja  = {{linktext|\u6734|\u667a|\u65fb}} \n| rr     = Bak Ji-min\n| mr     = Pak Chimin\n}} <!-- end module2 -->\n| signature          =\n}}\n\n'''Park Ji-min''' ({{Korean|hangul=\ubc15\uc9c0\ubbfc}}; born on October 13, 1995),<ref name=\"BTS profile\" /> better known mononymously as '''Jimin''', is a South Korean singer, songwriter, and dancer.  In 2013 he debuted as a member of the South Korean boy band [[BTS]], under the record label [[Big Hit Entertainment]].\n\n== Life and career ==\n=== Early life and education ===\nPark Ji-min ({{Korean|hangul=\ubc15\uc9c0\ubbfc}}) was born on October 13, 1995 in [[Geumjeong District]], [[Busan]], South Korea.<ref name=\"BTS profile\">{{Cite web|url=http://bts.ibighit.com/bts.php|title=BTS Profile|website=Big Hit Entertainment|language=ko|access-date=October 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151008024133/http://bts.ibighit.com/bts.php|archive-date=October 8, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> His immediate family includes mother, father, and a younger brother. When he was a child, he attended Busan's Hodong Elementary School and Yonsan Middle School.<ref>References for school and family:\n*{{cite web |title=[\ub354\uc2a4\ud0c0\ud504\ub85c\ud544] \ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8 \uc9c0\ubbfc \"'\ub7f0\ub2dd\ub9e8'\uc5d0 \ucd9c\uc5f0\ud558\uace0 \uc2f6\uc5b4\uc694\" |url=http://thestar.chosun.com/m/view.html?query=INEEDU&contid=2015043001518 |trans-title=[The Star Profile] I want to appear in 'Running Man' |work=The Star Chosun |accessdate=October 17, 2018 |language=Korean |date=April 30, 2015 |author=Eun Kyung Eun |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181024113028/http://thestar.chosun.com/m/view.html?query=INEEDU&contid=2015043001518 |archive-date=October 24, 2018 |url-status=dead }}\n*{{cite web |last1=Kim |first1=Soyeong |title=All School's Park Jimin Graduated From Have Closed |url=https://www.insight.co.kr/news/139663 |website=Insight |accessdate=October 22, 2018 |language=Korean |date=February 11, 2018 }}</ref> During middle school, he attended Just Dance Academy and learned popping and locking dance.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.blog.naver.com/PostView.nhn?blogId=poppinyun&logNo=221162128351&proxyReferer=https://m.search.naver.com/search.naver?query=%25EB%258D%2594%25EB%25B3%25B4%25EC%259D%25B4%25EC%25A6%2588&where=m&sm=mtp_hty|title=12\uc6d4\uc758 JUST DANCE \uc18c\uc2dd\u2502\ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8\uc758 \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8\uc640 \ub354\ubcf4\uc774\uc988\uc758 \uccab \ub370\ubdd4\ubb34\ub300|work=\ub124\uc774\ubc84 \ube14\ub85c\uadf8 {{!}} \ubd80\uc0b0\ub304\uc2a4\ud559\uc6d0 JUST DANCE \ub304\uc2a4\uc544\uce74\ub370\ubbf8|access-date=October 23, 2018|language=ko}}</ref> Prior to becoming a trainee, Jimin studied contemporary dance at Busan High School of Arts and was a top student in the modern dance department.<ref name=\"get to know\">{{cite web |last1=Herman |first1=Tamar |title=Get to Know BTS: Jimin |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/7850223/bts-jimin-get-to-know |work=[[Billboard.com]] | accessdate=October 17, 2018 |date=June 20, 2017}}</ref> After a teacher suggested he audition with an entertainment company, it led him to [[Big Hit Entertainment]]. Once he passed the auditions in 2012, he transferred to [[Korean Arts High School]], graduating in 2014.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dong |first1=Sun-hwa |title=Guess who? BTS members' pre-debut photos revealed [PHOTOS] |url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2018/10/732_257000.html |website=[[The Korea Times]] |accessdate=October 18, 2018 |date=October 15, 2018}}</ref> Jimin is currently enrolled at Global Cyber University.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ajeng |first1=Tisa |title=Meski Jadwal Super Sibuk, Ternyata BTS Telah Mendaftar Kuliah di Kampus ini, Bareng-bareng Loh! |url=http://style.tribunnews.com/2017/12/15/meski-jadwal-super-sibuk-ternyata-bts-telah-mendaftar-kuliah-di-kampus-ini-bareng-bareng-loh |website=Tribun News | location=Indonesia |accessdate=October 17, 2018 |language=Indonesian |date=December 15, 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== BTS ===\nOn June 13, 2013, Jimin made his debut as a member of [[BTS]] with the release of the single \"No More Dream\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/38336/bts-releases-debut-video|title=BTS Asks about Your Dreams in 'No More Dream' MV|author =Grace Danbi Hong|publisher=Mwave|date=June 12, 2013|accessdate=January 31, 2016}}</ref> In the group, Jimin holds the position of vocalist and dancer. Under BTS, he has released two solo tracks: \"Lie\" and \"[[Serendipity (BTS song)|Serendipity]]\". The song \"Lie\" was released in 2016 in the album ''[[Wings (BTS album)|Wings]]''. It was described as stunning and dramatic, conveying dark undertones and emotions that helped reflect the overall concept of the album.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.izm.co.kr/contentRead.asp?idx=28119&bigcateidx=1&subcateidx=3&view_tp=1|title=BTS \u2013 WINGS: Album Review|work=[[IZM]] |language=ko | author=Cho Jin-young | accessdate=April 16, 2017}}</ref> In contrast, \"Serendipity\" from the album ''[[Love Yourself: Her]]'' released in 2017 was soft and sensual, unraveling the joy, conviction, and curiosity of love.<ref>: References for \"Serendipity\":\n*{{cite web |last1=Kim |first1=Doohyeon |title=\"\ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8(BTS) \u2013 Love Yourself \u627f 'Her': Album Review\" |url=http://www.izm.co.kr/contentRead.asp?idx=28749&bigcateidx=1&subcateidx=3&view_tp=1 |website=[[IZM]] |accessdate=September 7, 2018}}\n*{{citeweb|url=http://www.star2.com/entertainment/2017/10/18/love-yourself-her-bts-music-review/|title=\u2018Love Yourself: Her\u2019: K-pop group BTS plays by the book|work=Star2 | publisher=[[The Star (Malaysia)]] | date=October 18, 2017|first=Chester | last=Chin | accessdate=October 24, 2017}}</ref>\n\nAll three of Jimin's solos \"Serendipity\", \"Lie\" and \"Serendipity (Full Length Edition)\" surpassed fifty million streams on [[Spotify]], making him the only Korean act to have three solo songs over 50 million streams.<ref>{{Cite news|title= BTS Member, Jimin, Sets Spotify Record With 3 Songs at 50 Million Streams Each |url=https://www.cheatsheet.com/entertainment/bts-member-jimin-sets-spotify-record-with-3-songs-at-50-million-streams-each.html/}}</ref> The songs were also the only solo songs by a BTS member in Official Chart's 20 most streamed BTS songs in the UK.<ref>{{Cite news|title= BTS \uc9c0\ubbfc, \u82f1(UK) \uc624\ud53c\uc15c \ucc28\ud2b8\uc640 '\uc2a4\ud3ec\ud2f0\ud30c\uc774'\uc11c \uc194\ub85c\uace1 '\ub77c\uc774' '\uc138\ub80c\ub514\ud53c\ud2f0'\ub85c \ucd5c\uace0 \uae30\ub85d \uc138\uc6cc |url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=022&aid=0003312005}}</ref> Jimin's song \"Promise\" (2018) saw SoundCloud's Biggest 24-Hour Debut Ever, surpassing the record set by Drake's \"Duppy Freestyle\", according to [[SoundCloud]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/tamarherman/2019/01/03/bts-jimins-solo-promise-sees-soundclouds-biggest-24-hour-debut-ever/#48996a4753d3|title=BTS's Jimin's Solo 'Promise' Sees Soundcloud's Biggest 24-Hour Debut Ever | publisher=[[Forbes]]}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, he was awarded the fifth-class Hwagwan [[Order of Cultural Merit (Korea)|Order of Cultural Merit]] by the [[President of South Korea]] along with other members of the group.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/ranking/read?oid=312&aid=0000354692|title='\ub300\uc911\ubb38\ud654\uc608\uc220\uc0c1' BTS, \ubb38\ud654\ud6c8\uc7a5 \ud654\uad00 \ucd5c\uc5f0\uc18c \uc218\ud6c8...\uc720\uc7ac\uc11d\ubd80\ud130 \u6545 \uae40\uc8fc\ud601\uae4c\uc9c0 '\uc601\uad11\uc758 \uc5bc\uad74\ub4e4' (\uc885\ud569)|access-date=October 25, 2018|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n=== Solo work ===\n\nIn 2014, Jimin collaborated with fellow member [[Jungkook]] for \"Christmas Day\", a Korean rendition of [[Justin Bieber]]'s \"[[Mistletoe (Justin Bieber song)|Mistletoe]]\", the Korean lyrics being written by Jimin.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://btsblog.ibighit.com/271|title=Christmas Day by \uc9c0\ubbfc.\uc815\uad6d|date=December 25, 2014|work=BANGTAN BLOG|access-date=October 21, 2018}}</ref> Later on, Jimin collaborated with Jungkook again by releasing a cover of \"[[We Don't Talk Anymore (Charlie Puth song)|We Don't Talk Anymore]]\", originally by [[Charlie Puth]] and [[Selena Gomez]], released on June 2, 2017.<ref name=\":0\">References for \"We Don't Talk Anymore\":\n\n*{{Cite news|url=http://btsblog.ibighit.com/364|title=We don't talk anymore PT 2 by Jimin&JK|date=June 3, 2017|work=BANGTAN BLOG|access-date=October 21, 2018}}\n*{{Cite web|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/music/news/a45689/jimin-and-jungkook-covering-selena-gomez-we-dont-talk-anymore/|title=Here's BTS's Jimin and Jungkook Covering Selena Gomez and Charlie Puth's 'We Don't Talk Anymore'|last=Bailey|first=Alyssa|date=June 2, 2017|website=Elle Magazine|access-date=October 21, 2018}}</ref>\n\nJimin began participating in a variety of shows such as ''[[Hello Counselor]]'', ''[[Please Take Care of My Refrigerator]]'', and ''God's Workplace'' in 2016.<ref name=\"variety shows\"/> In the same year, he began hosting as a special MC at shows such as ''[[Show! Music Core]]'' and ''[[M Countdown]]''.<ref name=\"Show! Music Core\"/><ref name=\"M Countdown\"/> During December he also participated in a duet at the [[KBS Song Festival]] with [[Lee Tae-min|Taemin]] from [[Shinee]].<ref name=\"KBS Song Festival\"/>\n\nJimin released his first solo song outside of BTS releases, \"Promise\", on December 30, 2018, for free on BTS' SoundCloud page.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/bts-jimin-releases-first-solo-single-promise-listen/|title=BTS\u2019 Jimin Releases First Solo Single, \u2018Promise\u2019: Listen|work=[[Us Weekly]]|last=Campbell|first=Kathy|date=December 30, 2018|accessdate=December 30, 2018}}</ref> The song, described by [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] as a \"mellow [[pop ballad]]\",<ref name=\"PromiseBil\">{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bts/8491752/bts-jimin-promise-song|title=BTS' Jimin Ends 2018 With Surprise Release of Solo Song 'Promise'|last=Herman|first=Tamar|date=December 30, 2018|accessdate=December 30, 2018|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> was composed by Jimin and Big Hit Entertainment producer Slow Rabbit, with the latter also producing the track.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/bts-jimin-surprises-fans-first-self-composed-solo-song-promise-2425389|title=BTS\u2019 Jimin surprises fans with first self-composed solo song \u2018Promise\u2019|work=[[NME]]|last=Daly|first=Rhian|date=December 30, 2018|accessdate=December 30, 2018}}</ref> \"Promise\" features lyrics written by Jimin and fellow BTS member [[RM (rapper)|RM]], and cover artwork photographed by bandmate [[V (singer)|V]].<ref name=\"PromiseBil\" />\n\n=== Philanthropy ===\n[[File:Jimin on Melon Music Awards 2016.jpg|Jimin performing \"[[Blood Sweat & Tears (BTS song)|Blood Sweat & Tears]]\" at the 2016 [[Melon Music Awards]].|alt=Jimin stands on a stage holding his belt while dancing.|thumb|right|upright]]\nFrom 2016 to 2018, Jimin supported graduates of Busan Hodong Elementary School, his alma mater, by covering uniform expenses. After news of the school's closing was released, he donated summer and winter middle school uniforms to the final graduates and gifted autographed albums to the entire student body.<ref>{{cite web |title=\ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8 \uc9c0\ubbfc, \ubaa8\uad50 \ud3d0\uad50 \uc18c\uc2dd\uc5d0 \uc0ac\uc778CD+\uad50\ubcf5 \uc120\ubb3c\u2026\ud6c8\ud6c8 \uc120\ud589 |url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=057&aid=0001226314 |via=[[Naver]] |accessdate=October 17, 2018 |language=Korean |date=February 20, 2018 | trans-title=Bangtan Boys Jimin, the birth of a school ... Leading to Hoon Hoon }}</ref> In early 2019, Jimin donated 100 million Korean won (roughly 88,000 US dollars) to the Busan Department of Education to help support lower income students. Of the total, \u20a930 million (roughly US$23,000) went to Busan Arts High School, Jimin's alma mater.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=241&aid=0002899735&lfrom=twitter|title=\ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8 \uc9c0\ubbfc, \ubd80\uc0b0\uad50\uc721\uccad\uc5d0 1\uc5b5\uc6d0 \uae30\ubd80 \ub4a4\ub2a6\uac8c \uc54c\ub824\uc838|trans-title=BTS member Jimin  donated 100 million won to the Busan Education Office|lang=ko|work=Daily Sports|last=Hwang|first=Ji-young|date=April 5, 2019|accessdate=April 5, 2019}}</ref> \n\n== Artistry ==\nJimin's vocals have been described as delicate and sweet.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hwang |first1=Hye-jin |title=\uc790\uc791\uace1 \u2018\uc57d\uc18d\u2019 \uc9c0\ud0a8 \ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8 \uc9c0\ubbfc, \ucda4\ub9cc \uc798\ucd94\ub294\uc904 \uc54c\uc558\ub2e4\uba74 \uc624\uc0b0[\ubba4\uc9c1\uc640\uce58] |url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=609&aid=0000038925 |website=[[Naver (corporation)|Naver]] |publisher=Newsen |accessdate=December 30, 2018 |language=Korean |date=December 31, 2018}}</ref> He is regarded as an exceptional dancer among the members of the group and in K-pop in general.<ref name=\"get to know\"/><ref name=\"elite daily\"/> Noelle Devoe of ''[[Elite Daily]]'' wrote that he is often praised for his \"smooth and elegant movements\" as well as his charm on stage. In the BTS documentary ''[[Burn the Stage: The Movie#Adaptation|Burn the Stage]]'', Jimin said that he thinks of himself as a perfectionist, stating even the smallest mistakes on stage makes him feel guilty and stresses him.<ref name=\"elite daily\"/>\n\nHe has cited singer [[Rain (entertainer)|Rain]] as one of his inspirations and reasons why he wanted to become both a singer and performer.<ref>{{cite web |title=K-pop News: BTS members, a comprehensive profile |url=https://www.politicalanalysis.co.za/k-pop-news-bts-members-a-comprehensive-profile/ |website=Political Analysis South Africa |accessdate=October 17, 2018 |date=April 8, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Impact and influence ==\nIn 2016, Jimin was ranked as the 14th most popular idol in an annual survey conducted by [[Gallup (company)|Gallup Korea]].<ref>{{cite web |title=2016\ub144 \uc62c\ud574\ub97c \ube5b\ub0b8 \uac00\uc218\uc640 \uac00\uc694 \u2013 \ucd5c\uadfc 10\ub144\uac04 \ucd94\uc774 \ud3ec\ud568, \uc544\uc774\ub3cc \uc120\ud638\ub3c4 |url=http://www.gallup.co.kr/gallupdb/reportContent.asp?seqNo=800&pagePos=1&selectYear=2016&search=&searchKeyword= |website=Gallop Korea |accessdate=December 18, 2018 |language=Korean |date=November 25, 2016}}</ref> He ranked 7th in 2017, before ranking 1st consecutively in 2018 and 2019.<ref>References for Gallup:\n*{{cite web |title=2017\ub144 \uc62c\ud574\ub97c \ube5b\ub0b8 \uac00\uc218\uc640 \uac00\uc694 \u2013 \ucd5c\uadfc 11\ub144\uac04 \ucd94\uc774, \uc544\uc774\ub3cc \uc120\ud638\ub3c4 \ud3ec\ud568 |url=http://www.gallup.co.kr/gallupdb/reportContent.asp?seqNo=886&pagePos=1&selectYear=2017&search=&searchKeyword= |website=Gallop Korea |accessdate=December 18, 2018 |language=Korean |date=December 19, 2017}}\n*{{cite web |title=\ud55c\uad6d\uac24\ub7fd \ub370\uc77c\ub9ac \uc624\ud53c\ub2c8\uc5b8, \ub9e4\uc8fc \uc0c8\ub85c\uc6b4 \uc5ec\ub860\uc870\uc0ac \uacb0\uacfc\ub97c \uc804\ud569\ub2c8\ub2e4. |url=https://gallupkorea.blogspot.com/2018/12/2018-12_18.html |website=Gallop Korea |accessdate=December 18, 2018 |language=Korean |date=December 18, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=https://www.gallup.co.kr/gallupdb/reportContent.asp?seqNo=1072|title=2019\ub144 \uc62c\ud574\ub97c \ube5b\ub0b8 \uac00\uc218\uc640 \uac00\uc694 \u2013 \ucd5c\uadfc 13\ub144\uac04 \ucd94\uc774 \ud3ec\ud568|date=December 19, 2019|website=Gallup Korea|access-date=December 19, 2019|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Jimin was the ninth most tweeted about celebrity and the eighth most tweeted about musician in the world.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Reitman |first1=Shelby |title=BTS Is 2018's Most Tweeted-About Celebrity, Plus More Year-End Twitter Data |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8488660/bts-most-tweeted-about-celebrity-twitter-2018-year-end-data |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=December 6, 2018 |date=December 5, 2018}}</ref> He was picked as the seventeenth best boyband member in history by ''[[The Guardian]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=The 30 best boyband members - ranked! |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/dec/13/the-30-best-boyband-members-ranked |website=The Guardian|accessdate=December 13, 2018}}</ref> From January to May 2018, Jimin won the monthly ''Peeper x Billboard'' Award for \"Top K-Pop Artist &ndash; Individual\". ''Peeper x Billboard'' is a collaboration between the ''Peeper'' social media app and [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'' Korea]], where it collects fan votes for their favorite K-pop artists and announces monthly winners. The prize was a donation to the charity [[UNICEF]] in his name.<ref>{{cite web |title=\ud53c\ud37c \uc120\uc815 2\uc6d4 \u2018\ucd5c\uace0 K-POP \uc544\ud2f0\uc2a4\ud2b8\u2019\uc5d0 \uc5d1\uc18c, \ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8 \u2018\uc9c0\ubbfc\u2019|url=https://news.joins.com/article/22543456 |website=News.Joins |accessdate=October 22, 2018 |language=Korean |date=April 17, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, he received a plaque of appreciation from the Cultural Conservation Society for performing [[buchaechum]], a traditional Korean fan dance, during the [[2018 Melon Music Awards]]. He received the award for helping spread the dance outside of Korea.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chu |first1=Yeong-joon |title=\u7f8e\ub9e4\uccb4 \"\ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8 \uc9c0\ubbfc '\uc804\uc124\uc801 \ubd80\ucc44\ucda4'\uc73c\ub85c \uac10\uc0ac\ud328 \ubc1b\uc744\ub9cc \ud588\ub2e4\" \uadf9\ucc2c |url=https://www.segye.com/newsView/20190228000760 |website=[[Segye Ilbo]] |accessdate=February 27, 2019 |language=Korean |date=February 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n[[File:Park Ji-min for Dispatch \"Boy With Luv\" MV behind the scene shooting, 15 March 2019 03.jpg|Jimin on the set of the \"[[Boy with Luv]]\" music video, March 2019.|alt=Jimin looks at the camera while sitting.|upright|thumb]]\n{{For|Jimin's works with [[BTS]]|BTS singles discography|BTS albums discography}}\n\n=== 